The paper focuses on the use of machine learning in computational science and engineering, specifically in the Oil and Gas industry. It addresses the issue of tracking provenance data throughout the ML lifecycle, which is a concern in data management and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a new data representation for provenance data in ML, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the ML lifecycle, which involves the use of various tools and workflows, and the need for proper tracking of data, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
